Accordingly, in one embodiment, there is a grounding disk having a top and a bottom for use on an airport hangar grounding point comprising:
a) a grounding connector on the bottom of the grounding disk capable of connecting to the airport hangar grounding point;
b) a plurality of connecting grounding points connected to the grounding connector, each connecting grounding point having a connection point on the top of the grounding disk for attachment to a grounding cable and positioned below the top of the grounding disk;
c) wherein the top surface of the grounding disk is tapered from a center of the top surface to a peripheral edge of the top surface; and
d) wherein the grounding disk can support at least 1000 lbf.
